The paper deals with lower bounds for arithmetic circuits, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also involves the analysis of matrices, which is a topic in both discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of the trace method is a technique used in algebraic complexity theory (cs.SC) and the problem of computing the dimension of the space of partial derivatives is a problem in computational algebraic geometry (cs.SY).
